# University Features for Clio

Adding features that make Clio a complete university-grade academic integrity platform. Prioritized by impact.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Feature 1: Student Submissions History Page

Students currently submit essays but have **no way to see their grades or feedback**. This is the #1 missing feature.

#### [NEW] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/submissions/page.tsx)

New `/submissions` page for students:
- Auth guard: only students can access
- Fetches the student's own submissions from `/api/submissions/mine`
- Displays a list of past submissions with: title, date, integrity score, grade (if graded), feedback
- Click to expand and read the full essay + detailed integrity report
- Visual indicators: grade badge, "Pending" / "Graded" status

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/api/submissions/mine/route.ts)

New `GET /api/submissions/mine` API route:
- Auth: student only
- Queries Supabase [submissions](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/backend/main.py#136-144) table filtered by `student_id`
- Joins `grades` table to include grade/feedback if present
- Returns submissions ordered by `submitted_at` descending

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/editor/page.tsx)

Add a "My Submissions" link/button in the editor header, so students can navigate to `/submissions`.

---

### Feature 2: Microsoft Outlook SSO for Students

Students will sign in with their **university Outlook / Microsoft 365 account**. This guarantees:
- Only students with a valid institutional email can access the platform
- No duplicate accounts (tied to university identity)
- Zero-friction onboarding (no manual registration)

Teachers continue using the existing username/password login.

#### Dependencies

- `next-auth` (Auth.js v5) — Microsoft/Azure AD provider
- Requires Azure AD App Registration (tenant ID, client ID, client secret)

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/api/auth/microsoft/route.ts)

Microsoft OAuth callback handler:
- Receives the OAuth code from Microsoft after student signs in
- Exchanges for access token, extracts email + display name
- **Auto-creates** a student profile in Supabase `profiles` on first login (username = email prefix, role = "student")
- Issues the existing HMAC session cookie (same as password login) for seamless compatibility
- Redirects to `/editor`

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/api/auth/microsoft/callback/route.ts)

Handles the OAuth2 redirect from Microsoft, exchanges auth code for token.

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/login/page.tsx)

Add a **"Sign in with University Email"** (Microsoft) button below the existing login form. The existing username/password form stays for teachers.

> [!NOTE]
> You will need to provide your **Azure AD / Microsoft Entra ID** credentials:
> - `MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID`
> - `MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET`
> - `MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID` (use your university's tenant, or `common` for any Microsoft account)
>
> These go in `.env.local`. I'll create the code infrastructure and prompt you for the values.

---

### Feature 3: Assignment Creator (Teacher)

Teachers should create structured assignments with instructions and deadlines, instead of letting students type free-form titles.

#### Supabase Migration — `assignments` table

New `assignments` table:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| [id](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/backend/main.py#30-52) | UUID PK | Auto-generated |
| `teacher_id` | UUID FK→profiles | Creator |
| `title` | TEXT | Assignment name |
| `description` | TEXT | Instructions / prompt |
| `due_date` | TIMESTAMPTZ | Deadline (nullable) |
| `max_word_count` | INTEGER | Optional word limit |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | Default now() |

Also add `assignment_id` (UUID FK→assignments, nullable) to [submissions](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/backend/main.py#136-144) table. The existing `assignment_title` remains for backward compatibility.

#### [NEW] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/assignments/page.tsx)

New `/assignments` page (teacher view):
- List all assignments created by this teacher
- Create new assignment: title, description (rich text or plain), optional due date, optional word limit
- Edit/delete existing assignments
- Shows submission count per assignment

#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/api/assignments/route.ts)

New CRUD API for assignments:
- `GET /api/assignments` — list assignments (teacher: own, student: all available)
- `POST /api/assignments` — create (teacher only)
- `PUT /api/assignments` — update (teacher only, own assignments)
- `DELETE /api/assignments` — delete (teacher only, own assignments)

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/editor/page.tsx)

Replace the free-text title input with an assignment selector dropdown:
- Fetches available assignments from `/api/assignments`
- Student picks an assignment → title, description, word limit auto-populate
- Still allows custom title as fallback for unassigned work
- Submission POSTs `assignment_id` alongside `assignment_title`

#### [MODIFY] [route.ts](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/api/submissions/route.ts)

Accept optional `assignment_id` in POST body. If provided, validate it exists and store it.

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/mini%20project/clio/frontend/app/dashboard/page.tsx)

Add "Assignments" link in header. Group submissions by assignment (using `assignment_id` instead of text-matching on title).

